com.jimmoores.quandl.util

Class DefaultRESTDataProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jimmoores.quandl.util.DefaultRESTDataProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RESTDataProvider

    public final class DefaultRESTDataProvider
extends Object
implements RESTDataProvider
    Utility methods for fetching data from remote Quandl REST interface. This is the default implementation that actually does a REST call, the other implementation is used for testing.

      • getJSONResponse

        public org.json.JSONObject getJSONResponse(javax.ws.rs.client.WebTarget target)
        Invoke a GET call on the web target and return the result as a parsed JSON object. Throws a QuandlUnprocessableEntityException if Quandl returned a response code that indicates a nonsensical request Throws a QuandlTooManyRequestsException if Quandl returned a response code indicating the client had made too many requests Throws a QuandlRuntimeException if there was a CSV parsing problem or response code was unusual
        Specified by:

      • getTabularResponse

        public TabularResult getTabularResponse(javax.ws.rs.client.WebTarget target)
        Invoke a GET call on the web target and return the result as a TabularResult (parsed CSV). Throws a QuandlUnprocessableEntityException if Quandl returned a response code that indicates a nonsensical request Throws a QuandlTooManyRequestsException if Quandl returned a response code indicating the client had made too many requests Throws a QuandlRuntimeException if there was a JSON parsing problem, network issue or response code was unusual
        Specified by:
        getTabularResponse in interface RESTDataProvider
